<br>
New genre games are a huge risk in comparison to a game that will bank big bucks. It's just like the movie industry. Summer blockbusters full of inane one liners and mind blowing special effects are the big money makers, and the artsy films are the ones that are revolutionary.<br>
<br>
Lets name some revolutionary video games from recent history:<br>
<br>
-The Sims (PC) - then branched into a million expansions, but lets not forget how original and unique the first game was<br>
<br>
- Homeworld (PC) - The original was critically acclaimed, and was absolutely amazing. It sold a whopping 80,000 copies. (That's bad)<br>
<br>
- Animal Crossing (Gamecube) <br>
<br>
- Cubivore (Gamecube) - have you ever heard of this one? It involved little low polygon animals eating other low polygon animals, to gain their power. The graphics sucked, but apparently the gameplay was extremely unique. <br>
<br>
- Pikmin (Gamecube) - this game is neat <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  A lot of people lump it in as a real time strategy game, but what it really truly is is a puzzle game. <br>
<br>
- Frequency (PS2) - Was unique in the universe, until its little brother Amplitude came out (Sequel)<br>
<br>
- Kirby's Tilt and Tumble (Gameboy Color) - This game involved moving the whole Gameboy to tilt and roll and jump kirby around. It is a marvel to play.<br>
<br>
Heck. Back when the original Tony Hawk came out, the extreme sports game genre was pretty much nonexistant. <br>
<br>
But very few of these unique games are commercial successes. The ones that I did list above are the ones that I do remember. Most of these are moderate successes commercially but the only one that was a huge success was the Sims. Most unique games are condemned to oblivion.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=tiestooakey>Tiesto Oakey</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Shadowknight who says Ni!</span><br>  Posts: 407<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(9/29/03 10:15 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4118.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Creativity in videogames</span><hr size=1> Just wait till worlds of warcraft comes out.<br>
